TEXT(beginproblem());
BEGIN_TEXT
    Give an example of a sequence of numbers such that each number in the
    sequence (after the first) is the sum of all the numbers that come before
    it.  What must be true about such a sequence?
$PAR
\{essay_box(4,60)\}
$PAR
END_TEXT

ANS(essay_cmp());

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR
Answers may vary. Sample answer:
Example: \(10, 10, 20, 40, 80, 160, \ldots\). Any such sequence must double at each successive term after the second.
END_SOLUTION

